  "text": "To estimate the error of a measured disk position, we follow the methods of Clement et al [CITATION_1] . We first assume an ideal, noise-free measurement of the template probe image I ref (r) is available, from careful measurements of the vacuum probe image. Next, we assume the measured image of a disk I(r) has a signal given by a Poisson distribution with a mean of n counts per pixel, and therefore also a variance of n. The variance σ x 2 of a cross-correlation measurement of the image translation error along the x direction is given by where D x is the normalized \"image roughness\" [CITATION_2] along the x direction, given by",
